## History
Following the Violet Dawn, there was a period in which the maintenance  and protection of Lamberton fell to the wayside. Crime ran rampant, increasing drastically the closer you got to the chasm. When it became apparent that [[Lamberton Campaign/The Families/The Parliament|the parliament]] and Benyl were busy maintaining control over large swathes of Ordeg, Romuloin Clay alongside his band of retired Mercenaries took it upon themselves to fill the void.  

A practical [[Official Material/Races/Dwarf|dwarf]], Romuloin did whatever was necessary to ensure the safety of streets that he started policing only got safer. This included execution of all criminals, even the petty ones, as well as those who found too much comfort in their newly secured streets and desserted. It took only a-few weeks before large swathes of the city were under Romuloin's control. As time passed though, and the seat of government's attention returned to the city Romuloin's newly formed group became key purveyors of protection and mercenary work in Lamberton, under the umbrella of Slowhand's Wall.  Since then, Romuloin has returned to retirement and passed the mantle onto his son, Fortren who was a young aspiring adventurer that returned home following the Violet Dawn when Romuloin and his band took to the streets.  

Since his father's retriement, Forten has largely succeeded in taking up his father's mantle. At the behest of [[Lamberton Campaign/The Families/The Parliament|the Parliament]] and supposedly following a long conversation with Benyl, Forten founded Blackheart's Band, a private mercenary company that is highly selective and highly sought after. With Benyl's blessing, Fortren has close ties to [[Lamberton Campaign/The Families/The Blue Core|the Blue Core]]  and his mercenaries are often deputized and hired out to [[Lamberton Campaign/The Families/The Blue Core|the Blue Core]] for more dangerous operations inside of Lamberton, Ordeg as a whole and even some more secret operations throughout Stolaria.

With this renown came opportunity for the Clay family. The Clay's have lived in Lamberton for a very long time, and while in recent years much of the family has taken to adventuring, they were renowned blacksmiths throughout Lamberton and throughout Stolaria in various circles. Members of his family have travelled the world and learned the various arts of blacksmithing. Fortren, more enterprise minded than his father, opened up various equipment shops and industrial forges in Lamberton and is now the foremost provider of equipment and material known for its durability in the city. Collectively, the smith shops as known as Larksbur's forge. For reasons unknown to the populace, usually credited to the skills learned by his family throughout their travels, no one's equipment is quite as good as the ones found at Larksbur's. In interviews with Fortren, he will often give credit to his family members but notably will also give credit to his worship of the Forge Loa.
## Notable Businesses
### Blackheart's Band
The mercenary group that formed following Romuloin's defense of the city. Becoming a mercenary in Blackheart's hand is no simple task, to do so requires defeating a current sitting member of which there are 250. Should one manage to join the band though, their work will be highly sought after and well compensated. It is even said that Forten will occasionally do work for Benyl and those Benyl refers. 

### Larksbur's Forge
The most rewowned collection of smiths in the city. Commonly sought after for various projects done by the Artificer's college as well as various adventuring parties.  It is said that the wares found in Larksbur's shop will last a lifetime and help many heroes and soldiers make a name for themselves.
